# ⏱ Time & Space Complexity

### Time Complexity:

For each character (n times), we expand up to n.

👉 **O(n²)**

### Space Complexity:

We only store result string.

👉 **O(1)** (ignoring output)

---

# 🎯 Why This Works

* Every palindrome has a center.
* There are only `2n - 1` possible centers.
* Expanding from center avoids checking all substrings.
* Much better than brute force (O(n³)).

---

# 🧩 Alternative Method: DP (Dynamic Programming)

DP uses a 2D table:
`dp[i][j] = True` if substring from i to j is palindrome.

But:

* Time → O(n²)
* Space → O(n²)
* More memory heavy

👉 Expand Around Center is cleaner and optimal for interviews.

